WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.040
So we've heard about the new exciting drugs, and now we're going to go back in time and talk about autologous stem cell transplants, and is there still a role, or is it dead?

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:21.160
So looking historically at previous studies, you can look at these curves and say, yeah, they look similar shapes to all the curves we've seen in the prior talks.

00:00:21.300 --> 00:00:24.720
The difference is the x-axis is in years, not in months.

00:00:24.880 --> 00:00:33.100
You can see median progression-free survival following autologous stem cell transplant of almost a decade in multiple studies,

00:00:33.100 --> 00:00:44.980
and then subsequently the benefit of maintenance rituximab was established in the LEMA study with a seven-year progression-free survival of 79% in the group that received rituximab maintenance.

00:00:46.180 --> 00:00:49.280
These are three studies of real-world data.

00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:54.860
What's striking in these studies is that less than half of the patients,

00:00:54.880 --> 00:01:01.120
and the first two studies who were eligible for autologous transplant actually underwent autologous transplant.

00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:08.640
The first column is the MCL consortium, all academic centers, about a little over 500 patients.

00:01:08.760 --> 00:01:15.380
Only a third actually went transplant, and they showed that transplant was a significant predictor of outcome,

00:01:15.380 --> 00:01:21.600
and the top curve in purple is the patient group that received a citerabine induction.

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:24.760
The middle column is the flat iron database.

00:01:24.880 --> 00:01:28.120
Predominantly community centers, over 3,000 patients.

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:32.760
In that study, only 25% of eligible patients underwent transplant,

00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:37.840
and the median overall survival was similar in both groups,

00:01:37.840 --> 00:01:43.720
and the time to next treatment also showed no advantage with autologous stem cell transplant.

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:53.020
The last column is 25 centers, predominantly academic, higher number of patients undergoing transplant at 67% of eligible patients,

00:01:53.020 --> 00:01:53.120
and they showed that transplant was a significant predictor of outcome, and the time to next treatment also showed no advantage with autologous stem cell transplant.

00:01:53.120 --> 00:01:53.120
The last column is 25 centers, predominantly academic, higher number of patients undergoing transplant at 67% of eligible patients,

00:01:53.120 --> 00:01:53.240
and they showed that transplant was a significant predictor of outcome,

00:01:53.240 --> 00:01:53.340
and the time to next treatment also showed no advantage with autologous stem cell transplant.

00:01:53.340 --> 00:01:53.340
The last column is 25 centers, predominantly academic, higher number of patients undergoing transplant at 67% of eligible patients,

00:01:53.340 --> 00:01:59.680
and they showed that transplant was associated with a progression-free survival benefit, but not overall survival.

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.660
Then we get to some more modern studies.

00:02:03.660 --> 00:02:07.720
The ECOG study looked at do all patients need autologous stem cell transplant.

00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:10.000
Most of us are probably familiar with this study.

00:02:10.380 --> 00:02:13.920
Patients received an induction regimen of the physician's choice,

00:02:14.320 --> 00:02:18.920
and then at the end of study, they had an MRD assessment in the peripheral blood.

00:02:19.380 --> 00:02:22.020
If they were MRD positive or indeterminate,

00:02:22.300 --> 00:02:22.440
if they were MRD positive or indeterminate,

00:02:22.440 --> 00:02:22.500
if they were MRD positive or indeterminate,

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:23.320
if they were MRD positive or indeterminate,

00:02:23.340 --> 00:02:26.020
if they were MRD negative,

00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:29.520
they were randomized to transplant versus no transplant.

00:02:30.360 --> 00:02:34.000
The first curve shows arm A versus arm B,

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:37.500
and you can see that the lines are superimposable,

00:02:37.660 --> 00:02:41.000
showing that there was no benefit, at least in the short term,

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:46.520
at three years for patients undergoing transplant if they were MRD negative.

00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:51.620
This was presented as a late-breaking abstract last in 2024 at ASH.

00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:57.720
In the subsequent patients who were MRD positive or MRD indeterminate,

00:02:57.720 --> 00:03:03.460
they underwent transplant, and their three-year progression-free survival was about 75%.

00:03:03.460 --> 00:03:11.980
The TRIANGLE study also looked at can we replace autologous stem cell transplant with a BTK inhibitor.

00:03:12.300 --> 00:03:13.600
So it was a three-arm study.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:16.720
Induction was RCHOP alternating with RDHAP.

00:03:17.660 --> 00:03:21.640
In arm one, it was standard of care, RCHOP alternating with RDHAP,

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:24.980
for a total of six cycles, followed by autologous stem cell transplant,

00:03:25.180 --> 00:03:26.180
and then observation.

00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:34.240
Arm two added ibrutinib to the RCHOP arm and still received transplant,

00:03:34.460 --> 00:03:37.140
followed then by two years of ibrutinib maintenance.

00:03:37.620 --> 00:03:40.220
And then the bottom arm added ibrutinib,

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:46.420
but took out transplant and then still had two years of ibrutinib maintenance.

00:03:46.840 --> 00:03:50.820
What the study showed is that autologous transplant plus ibrutinib

00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:53.660
was superior to autologous transplant only.

00:03:54.560 --> 00:04:00.320
Autologous transplant plus ibrutinib was not superior to ibrutinib without transplant.

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:04.220
Autologous transplant is not superior to ibrutinib.

00:04:05.060 --> 00:04:09.640
And ibrutinib without transplant was superior to autologous transplant.

00:04:09.880 --> 00:04:14.140
And then the curve at the bottom right in red,

00:04:14.140 --> 00:04:19.740
there was a superior overall survival with autologous transplant plus ibrutinib,

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:23.180
or ibrutinib alone, compared with transplant.

00:04:23.340 --> 00:04:26.780
So both ibrutinib-containing arms were better than transplant.

00:04:27.260 --> 00:04:30.160
The study was subsequently amended about halfway through

00:04:30.160 --> 00:04:31.940
to add in maintenance for teximab,

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:35.000
and about half the patients received maintenance for teximab.

00:04:36.220 --> 00:04:40.320
Does anyone benefit from autologous transplant in the triangle study?

00:04:40.460 --> 00:04:43.100
Although this was non-statistical benefit,

00:04:43.500 --> 00:04:49.180
you can see that the curves that added in transplant to the ibrutinib

00:04:49.180 --> 00:04:56.560
did have a higher PFS curve in both the KI-67 as well as the P53-positive,

00:04:56.720 --> 00:04:58.780
a little bit less than the blastoid variant.

00:05:00.480 --> 00:05:03.660
This is our Mayo Clinic data of over 25 years,

00:05:03.880 --> 00:05:06.920
looking at 303 patients who underwent transplant.

00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:11.560
Again, obviously, slope to the curve here, no plateau,

00:05:11.560 --> 00:05:15.920
but you can see that the x-axis is going out to 20 years.

00:05:16.300 --> 00:05:18.960
So the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.060 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:19.160
and the median follow-up was 11.2 years,

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:22.760
and our median progression-free survival was just under a decade.

00:05:23.900 --> 00:05:27.300
Looking at the high-risk patients, they had a shorter PFS,

00:05:27.680 --> 00:05:30.500
but even if they only had one high-risk factor,

00:05:30.840 --> 00:05:34.440
the median progression-free survival was still 7.7 years.

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:37.460
So these are still very durable remissions,

00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:39.820
even though they're not curative.

00:05:42.420 --> 00:05:47.400
TP53 mutated mantle cell lymphoma does not benefit from autologous transplant.

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:49.140
So that group,

00:05:49.140 --> 00:05:51.840
which is typically not taken to transplant.

00:05:53.400 --> 00:05:55.960
This was recently presented at EBMT,

00:05:56.040 --> 00:05:58.540
and if we just focus on the top half of the slide,

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:00.720
you can see their approach.

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:05.800
So if you have access to BTK in the first line in high-risk,

00:06:05.980 --> 00:06:09.080
they still recommend autologous transplant.

00:06:09.340 --> 00:06:11.920
In the standard risk, transplant is not done.

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:16.820
If you don't have access to a BTK in either high-risk or standard risk,

00:06:16.820 --> 00:06:18.820
the plan is still to go to autologous transplant,

00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:23.480
and they have not incorporated the MRD data into their approach.

00:06:24.580 --> 00:06:28.660
This is kind of taking all of the studies and creating a hybrid approach.

00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:30.160
So we have the ECOG approach,

00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:33.900
which is just based on MRD on the left-hand side.

00:06:34.100 --> 00:06:36.500
We have the triangle approach with the BTK,

00:06:36.740 --> 00:06:41.740
with the alternating ARCHOP and RRD-HAP not incorporating transplant.

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:43.300
Although I question,

00:06:43.300 --> 00:06:47.380
could you still consider it for the high-risk patients and perhaps maybe

00:06:47.380 --> 00:06:48.700
incorporate the MRD?

00:06:48.940 --> 00:06:50.600
And then it comes to the hybrid approach,

00:06:50.600 --> 00:06:54.580
which basically induction chemotherapy of your choice,

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:57.380
typically more of a BR-based regimen,

00:06:57.380 --> 00:06:58.960
plus or minus a BTK,

00:07:00.220 --> 00:07:02.920
but in the MRD-guided transplant,

00:07:03.220 --> 00:07:05.560
if undetectable MRD,

00:07:05.560 --> 00:07:06.520
no transplant,

00:07:06.520 --> 00:07:07.700
if still detectable,

00:07:07.980 --> 00:07:12.780
then perhaps consider a transplant and then add rituximab and BTK maintenance

00:07:12.880 --> 00:07:13.620
at the end.

00:07:14.940 --> 00:07:15.520
And thank you.
